The article is a letter from President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House, providing a six-month consolidated report on military operations conducted by the United States Armed Forces in support of counterterrorism objectives. The letter highlights ongoing operations in Afghanistan, Iraq, Syria, Somalia, Yemen, and Cuba. It also mentions military operations related to the Lord's Resistance Army, military operations in Egypt, Jordan, and Kosovo, and regional security operations in Yemen, Libya, and the Central African Republic. The President states that these operations are conducted in coordination with international partners and are aimed at protecting U.S. citizens and interests. He emphasizes that the deployments are carried out within the framework of his constitutional and statutory authority as Commander in Chief.